This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and reinforcement learning, which are both subfields of computer science. The paper specifically focuses on dependency parsing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of reinforcement learning also suggests that the paper could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of the Stanford Neural Dependency Parser, which involves computer vision techniques, indicating that the paper could also fall under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
